{"body": "But I think you can do the same thing using proc/lambda\n\n```ruby\nclass PaymentRevenue < ActiveRecord::Base\n  belongs_to :payment\n  belongs_to :revenue\n\n  validates :revenues, inclusion: { in: -> { |record| record.available_revenues } }\n\n  def available_revenues\n    payment.revenue.children\n  end\nend\n```\n\nI'm not against neither in favor. I'm just want to know if this is adding feature or is only syntax sugar.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/7679837", "created_at": "2012-08-12T21:09:47Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7342#issuecomment-7679837", "updated_at": "2012-08-12T21:09:47Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7342, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/rafaelfranca", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/0525b332aafb83307b32d9747a93de03?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F2c7b84fa30f0cea96a90729afe2970a0.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/received_events", "gravatar_id": "0525b332aafb83307b32d9747a93de03", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "rafaelfranca", "type": "User", "id": 47848, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523df5adbd354364b900bcbb"}, "id": 7679837, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7342"}
